    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe `vim` color scheme shipped with Neovim is meant to reproduce the original Vim default theme as closely as possible. It's important that it does, because many pre-Neovim color schemes rely on some of its definitions, and so the easiest way to \"port\" them to Neovim is to just have them load the `vim.lua` file that defines it (which is also [recommended by `:help colorscheme`](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/c7d13f2895fa657ff3d9d45741f9abec25072b56/runtime/doc/syntax.txt#L4851-L4855)).\n\nWhile the scheme does match Vim's default scheme for the most part, they do differ in how visual selections look (`Visual` highlight group):\n\n<table>\n<tr>\n<th>Vim default</th>\n<th>Neovim with <code>vim</code> color scheme</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<img src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/74f9bbc1-6cc8-4de6-9c0b-508396a3ec68\" alt=\"Vim default color scheme\">\n</td>\n<td>\n<img src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/4c1d3421-0e19-409f-b7ca-12f5ac67786a\" alt=\"Neovim 'vim' color scheme\">\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n\nAs you can see, in Vim, the foreground color remains unchanged so that the syntax highlighting remains visible (i.e. foreground color `NONE`), while in Neovim, the foreground color is a monochrome black.\n\n(The background color is also a bit darker in Neovim, but I don't consider that as important, as most themes will override this anyway, while not all override the foreground color.)\n\nIt would be great if this could be fixed.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Open some code with syntax highlighting activated in both editor & config combinations (with no extra config loaded):\n    a. Vim with default color scheme: `vim -u NONE +'set notermguicolors' +'syntax on' /path/to/some/code-file`\n    b. Neovim with `vim` color scheme: `nvim -u NONE +'colorscheme vim' +'set notermguicolors' +'syntax on' /path/to/some/code-file`\n2. Visually select some characters in the buffer that exhibit varied syntax highlighting to see the difference.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nVisual selections in Neovim with the `vim` color scheme applied should look the same as in Vim with its default color scheme applied. Or at least the foreground should keep its syntax highlighting instead of turning monochrome.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.10.4\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 9.0\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nDebian Linux 12\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\ngnome-terminal 3.46.8\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nPrebuilt binary Tarball from GitHub releases",
